Emergency services have been called to the scene of a large fire at a "derelict building".Hertfordshire Fire and Rescue Service said the fire could be seen from Lieutenant Ellis Way and the A10 in Cheshunt, Hertfordshire but did not confirm the exact location of the blaze.The service said that eight fire engines are on the scene, and are being supported by the London Fire Brigade while they contain the fire.It said the fire was "under control" and that there were no casualties, but asked people living nearby to "avoid the area where possible".
Hertfordshire Police said it was "monitoring local road closures" because of the incident.
